adjectives.description: compunctious (comparative more compunctious, superlative most compunctious)

entries.meaning: Exhibiting compunctions, scruples, feelings of guilt.
examples: That tend on mortal thoughts, unsex me here;
And fill me, from the crown to the toe, top-full
Of direst cruelty! make thick my blood,
Stop up the access and passage to remorse,
That no compunctious visitings of nature
Shake my fell purpose, nor keep peace between
